{"TopicId":186577,"ForumId":18,"TopicTitle":"The Upcoming Movies (and Movie Trailers) MegaThread!","CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-21T18:35:42Z","PageNum":24,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-13T02:50:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m unapologetically watching 1899 with the English dubs on everybody. If I want to read everything everybody\u0027s saying I\u0027ll pick up a book.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes they\u0027re poor in a lot of places but they\u0027ve a lot more emotion than letters on the screen, and now I get to see what\u0027s happening AND know what people are saying. At the same time!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-12-13T02:51:04Z\u0022 title=\u002212/13/2022 02:51  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 13, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by Superfluous J\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-13T04:59:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224208290\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186577\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221670899852\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m unapologetically watching 1899 with the English dubs on everybody. If I want to read everything everybody\u0027s saying I\u0027ll pick up a book.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes they\u0027re poor in a lot of places but they\u0027ve a lot more emotion than letters on the screen, and now I get to see what\u0027s happening AND know what people are saying. At the same time!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFIe!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will add: as you progress through the city you discover that the Babel of languages is an integral part of the storytelling\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-13T05:22:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s strange...\u003Cbr\u003E\nI was sure that in 1899 all of them are speaking in Russian.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nuke","CreatedById":10883,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-13T06:51:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nidk i watch a lot of foreign films and i think i enjoyed them with subtitles more than dubs, especially since there are many without dubs.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni do take a few exceptions to languages that are spoken very quickly or films that are dialog heavy, as im a slow reader. spanish and italian for example is very hard to follow.\u00A0i might enable dubs if i have to rewind a lot.\u00A0dark and 1899 are both paced well for subtitles and you can read without missing too much.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhat i do not like is excessive subtitles in domestic films to artificially make a film more diverse. i like the way they did it in the hunt for red october, they start in russian and once they established that the characters are russian, switch to english.\u00A0 1899 was doing something different, and i thought it was just as clever.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-14T01:39:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224208317\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186577\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221670907542\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 hours ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFIe!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will add: as you progress through the city you discover that the Babel of languages is an integral part of the storytelling\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI trust that even though I cannot speak 30 languages, I\u0027m intelligent enough to recognize when the characters are unable to understand each other when the time comes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-14T02:57:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224208636\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186577\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221670981962\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n53 minutes ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI trust that even though I cannot speak 30 languages, I\u0027m intelligent enough to recognize when the characters are unable to understand each other when the time comes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFie AGAIN!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFie!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou are missing out on the \u0027killer app\u0027 of the show (to use the parlance you kids these days might understand).\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:9px;\u0022\u003EThe Babel is practically the raison d\u0027etre of the show!\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrankly - the show is ...okay.\u00A0 It has some really interesting elements and I\u0027m pretty sure the show runners were counting on at least two seasons to tell the story they wanted to tell.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s like \u0027The OA\u0027 - a show that was compelling, unique and very well acted - but that kind of got lost in itself or could not get past a certain thin-ness in the writing/underlying story.\u00A0 They wanted to get cute with a thing but couldn\u0027t find a way past to something deeper.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0027Dark\u0027 on the other hand was really well done and managed (in most ways) to navigate those problems.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-14T04:47:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn the 1899 multilingual communication.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003E(Spoiler warning)\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003E(No, seriously, a spoiler).\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs all of them are virtual characters, why would they speak in different languages?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo the NPC not understand each other?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022American components. Russian components. All made in Taiwan!\u0022 (c)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey should think in Chinese.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nuke","CreatedById":10883,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-14T05:17:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224208684\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186577\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221670993262\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn the 1899 multilingual communication.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003E(Spoiler warning)\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003E(No, seriously, a spoiler).\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs all of them are virtual characters, why would they speak in different languages?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo the NPC not understand each other?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022American components. Russian components. All made in Taiwan!\u0022 (c)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey should think in Chinese.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni think that the simulation is part training drills and part behavioral experiment. i have a feeling there is something wrong with the \u0022real\u0022 prometheus and that the people on board are not equipped to handle the situation.\u00A0 multiple iterations seem to have been conducted. the use of multiple languages could be part of the experiment or it could just be that the ship has a diverse population just like the simulation. i have a hunch that all the characters who killed themselves were npcs and dont have a real world counterpart, or perhaps their real world counterparts are no longer alive. perhaps the simulation was meant as a form of stasis but had the unintended side effect of erasing everyone\u0027s memory,\u00A0 the fake persona takes over the real one and therefore can no longer operate the prometheus.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-14T14:45:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00221670958136176621908.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022113.19\u0022 height=\u0022918\u0022 width=\u0022811\u0022 src=\u0022https://cs13.pikabu.ru/post_img/big/2022/12/13/11/1670958136176621908.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-17T19:55:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/bHXejJq5vr0?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u002265 \u2013\u00A0Official Trailer (HD)\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Just Jim","CreatedById":148725,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-17T21:22:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224210083\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186577\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221671306945\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/bHXejJq5vr0?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u002265 \u2013\u00A0Official Trailer (HD)\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, this one caught my eye yesterday... It look\u0027s just different enough it might be really good\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd from the writers of \u0022A Quiet Place\u0022???\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nIt will be very interesting to see Adam Driver in something that maybe isn\u0027t horribly written.\u00A0 \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-17T22:18:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224210119\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186577\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221671312136\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022148725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Just Jim\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n49 minutes ago, Just Jim said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsomething that maybe isn\u0027t horribly written\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich sci-fi / space movies do you think have the best scriptwriting / story? Any (recent) favorites?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think Prometheus is great, but only if you see all the events as being narrated by David.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nuke","CreatedById":10883,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-18T01:31:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224210083\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186577\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221671306945\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/bHXejJq5vr0?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u002265 \u2013\u00A0Official Trailer (HD)\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso planet of the apes, but with dinosaurs.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Just Jim","CreatedById":148725,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-18T01:35:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224210139\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186577\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221671315504\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/17/2022 at 5:18 PM, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich sci-fi / space movies do you think have the best scriptwriting / story? Any (recent) favorites?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think Prometheus is great, but only if you see all the events as being narrated by David.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI really liked Prometheus. And I agree about David, and Alien: Covenant. You really need to see the extended versions for it all to make sense.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nI could go on for hours about what I think is well written or not (and why) but if I have to pick a favorite recent sci-fi movie for writing, I think I\u0027m going with \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EShin: Godzilla\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/em\u003E. I know it\u0027s hard to find, sorry, but it\u0027s well worth it, IMO. It really captures the feel of the original Gojira, and also the real-time fears of\u00A0Fukushima. This is not your average campy Godzilla movie (IMO). Great writing (for a Godzilla\u00A0 movie).\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd to bring this back on-topic, I\u0027ve heard rumors there might be an upcoming sequel in the works.\u00A0\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nSpoiler: From \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EShin: Godzilla\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/em\u003E, one of the scariest scenes ever... and I\u0027ve seen them all.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents ipsClearfix\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allow=\u0022accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/iUaoMe7QPVg?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022Shin Godzilla Atomic Breath | Shin Godzilla (2016) [8K Upscale]\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-12-19T01:27:22Z\u0022 title=\u002212/19/2022 01:27  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 19, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by Just Jim\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-18T05:26:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n65\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u0026lt;...\u0026gt;\u003Cbr\u003E\nLed to prehistoric Earth.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003E\u0026lt;dinos and robots fighting\u003C/em\u003E\u0026gt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003E(Recalls the \u0022Butterfly Effect\u0022)\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nA butterfly?.. Did one say \u0022BUTTERFLY\u0022?..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nuke","CreatedById":10883,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-19T05:40:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ncurrently looking forward to \u0022cocaine bear\u0022. the preview could not be 